Danny Burch, a United States citizen who had been held hostage in Yemen for 18 months, has been recovered and reunited with his wife and children. The United Arab Emirates played a crucial role in bringing Danny back home. This successful recovery highlights the collaborative efforts of the United States and its partners. The US government, along with its foreign partners, prioritizes the safe return of American hostages and has secured freedom for 20 American captives since the President's election victory. The administration remains committed to bringing back the remaining American hostages.